# slugbase-docs: Documentation Boundaries

This repo is the **source of truth for customer-facing documentation**. It is built and hosted by **Documentation.AI** from `docs/` and `docs/documentation.json`, with two strictly separated trees.

- **Self-hosted** (`docs/selfhosted/`, URLs `/selfhosted/...`): Document only features and flows available to self-hosted deployments. No SaaS features (plans, billing, orgs, cloud-only signup, feature limits) in this section.
- **Cloud** (`docs/cloud/`, URLs `/cloud/...`): Document SaaS features, plans, billing, and cloud-only behavior. Do not move cloud-only content into `docs/selfhosted/`.
- When documenting a feature, state clearly whether it applies to **self-hosted**, **cloud**, or **both**. Do not blur the boundary.

For full workspace architecture and documentation rules, see **slugbase** `.cursor/rules/workspace-architecture.mdc`.
